sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Maintainer as Repository Maintainer
    participant GH as GitHub Events
    participant Queue as Actions Job Queue
    participant BuildJob as Actions Runner (build job)
    participant Buildx as docker/build-push-action
    participant Docker as Docker Engine
    participant Builder as resume-builder:ci container
    participant UV as uv
    participant BuilderPy as src/build.py
    participant YAML as src/data.yaml
    participant Jinja as Jinja2 Renderer
    participant Latex as pdflatex
    participant Artifact as upload-pages-artifact
    participant DeployJob as Actions Runner (deploy job)
    participant Deploy as deploy-pages action
    participant PagesAPI as GitHub Pages Deployment API
    participant Pages as GitHub Pages CDN
    actor Visitor as Resume Visitor

    Note over GH,Queue: Entry points implemented: push to main, workflow_dispatch.
    Maintainer->>GH: Push commit to main (or manually dispatch workflow)
    GH->>Queue: Enqueue workflow run (concurrency group: pages)
    Queue->>BuildJob: Start build job when runner is available

    BuildJob->>BuildJob: actions/checkout@v4
    BuildJob->>BuildJob: actions/configure-pages@v5
    BuildJob->>Buildx: Initialize Buildx
    Buildx->>Docker: Build Dockerfile with GHA cache
    alt Image build succeeds
        Docker-->>BuildJob: resume-builder:ci available
    else Image build fails
        Docker-->>BuildJob: Build error
        BuildJob->>GH: Mark workflow failed with logs
    end

    BuildJob->>Builder: docker run ... sh -lc "uv sync --frozen && uv run src/build.py"
    Builder->>UV: Sync locked Python dependencies
    UV->>BuilderPy: Execute build.py
    BuilderPy->>YAML: Load YAML content
    BuilderPy->>BuilderPy: Validate required top-level keys
    alt Validation passes
        BuilderPy->>Jinja: Render template.tex with custom delimiters
        Jinja-->>BuilderPy: generated.tex content
        BuilderPy->>Latex: Compile generated.tex via pdflatex
        alt pdflatex returncode == 0
            Latex-->>BuilderPy: generated.pdf
            BuilderPy->>BuilderPy: Rename generated.pdf -> resume.pdf
            BuilderPy->>BuilderPy: Delete generated.aux + generated.log
        else pdflatex returncode != 0
            Latex-->>BuilderPy: Compilation failure output
            BuilderPy->>GH: Print truncated pdflatex log and exit 1
            BuildJob->>GH: Mark workflow failed
        end
    else Validation fails
        BuilderPy->>GH: Raise ValueError and fail run
        BuildJob->>GH: Mark workflow failed
    end

    opt Build artifacts prepared on success
        BuildJob->>BuildJob: Create _site/
        par Static site assembly
            BuildJob->>BuildJob: Copy resume.pdf to _site/
        and Landing page generation
            BuildJob->>BuildJob: Write static _site/index.html
        end
        BuildJob->>Artifact: Upload artifact (name: resume-pages)
    end

    BuildJob-->>DeployJob: needs: build satisfied
    DeployJob->>Deploy: actions/deploy-pages@v4
    Deploy->>PagesAPI: Create deployment with artifact + OIDC token
    alt Deployment accepted
        PagesAPI-->>Deploy: Deployment created
        Deploy->>Pages: Publish new static content
        DeployJob->>GH: Mark workflow success + page URL
    else Deployment rejected (e.g., Pages disabled/misconfigured)
        PagesAPI-->>Deploy: 4xx/5xx error
        DeployJob->>GH: Mark workflow failed with API error
    end

    Visitor->>Pages: GET /latest-resume/ or /resume.pdf
    Note over Pages: Runtime serving is static file hosting only.
    Note over Pages: No custom middleware/authz/DB/business service layer exists in this repository.
    Pages-->>Visitor: Static response or HTTP error

    opt Observability hooks currently available
        GH->>Maintainer: Workflow status, step logs, and failure traces in Actions UI
    end
